  "text": "Plant Growth and Preparation of Thylakoid Membranes-A. thaliana (ecotype Wassilewskija) was cultivated hydrophonically [CITATION_1] for 12 weeks in a 10/14-h light/dark regime. The thylakoid membranes were isolated from the leaves harvested in the daytime (1.5 h after the light was turned on) essentially according to the protocol [CITATION_2] . The isolated thylakoids were washed twice with 10 mM sodium pyrophosphate (pH 7.8), then were washed twice with 30 mM sodium phosphate (pH 7.8), 5 mM MgCl 2 , 50 mM NaCl, 100 mM sucrose, and finally were washed twice with 25 mM NH 4 HCO 3 .",
